### Key Implementation Details

**PalmCareAIApp.swift:**
- Global `UINavigationBarAppearance` in `init()`: white bg, palmText titles, palmBorder shadow, palmPrimary tint
- Face ID lock screen: shows `FaceIDLockScreen` if `useFaceID` is true and not yet unlocked
- `onChange(of:)` uses iOS 16-compatible single-parameter closure syntax

**AudioRecorderService.swift:**
- Format: M4A (AAC), 44100Hz, mono, 128kbps
- Saved to Documents/Recordings/
- Background recording: reads `@AppStorage("backgroundRecording")` — when enabled, disables idle timer during recording
- Timers added to `RunLoop.common` mode for background operation
- Bluetooth support: `.allowBluetoothA2DP`
- iOS 17+ uses `AVAudioApplication.requestRecordPermission()`
- iOS 16 fallback uses `AVAudioSession.requestRecordPermission()`

**Google Calendar OAuth (in-app):**
- Uses `ASWebAuthenticationSession` for native OAuth flow
- Redirect URI: `{api.baseURL}/calendar/mobile-callback` (backend endpoint)
- Backend `/calendar/mobile-callback` receives Google auth code, redirects to `com.palmcare.ai://oauth2callback?code=...`
- URL scheme `com.palmcare.ai` registered in Info.plist
- Google Cloud Console must have redirect URI: `https://api-production-a0a2.up.railway.app/calendar/mobile-callback`

**ContractsView.swift:**
- Documents grouped by client name
- Client sections collapsed by default, expand on tap
- Filter tabs: All, Contracts, Notes, Audio
- QuickLook preview for viewing documents
- Authenticated download via bearer token

**Settings Toggles (AppStorage keys):**
- `useFaceID` — Face ID login
- `notificationsEnabled` — Notifications
- `backgroundRecording` — Keep recording when screen locks (off by default)
- `appTheme` — Theme display (default "Light")
- `googleCalendarConnected` — Google Calendar status

